on poor old Gerry Adamson, a great guy, andthat Louise was free. Too free in fact. An urgent letter I now wrote her,summoning her back to Quirn at once, for a serious Discussion of a matterconcerning both her and me, reached her only after describing a comic circlevia four fashionable spots on the Continent. I never saw the wire she saidshe sent me from New York on October 1.

On October 2, an abnormally warm day, the first of a week-long series,Mrs. King telephoned in the afternoon to invite me